    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01156.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Camden<ptr target="loc.01156_n1"/></name> 
                    <date when="1887-07-22">July 22, '87</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Your letter to H G<ptr target="n0262"/> is rec'd 
           &amp; he has shown it to me&#8212;He is 
           here yet painting the portrait. 
           &#8212;<hi rend="underline">W</hi>m O'C<ptr target="n2002"/> has got back to Wash'n.
           &#8212;he is very poorly &#8212;nearly utterly 
           disabled in leg-power (walking or 
           even standing)&#8212;Eldridge<ptr target="n0210"/> is at Los Angeles 
           to stay&#8212;Three or four weeks of fearful 
           heat here, but I have stood it &amp; am fairly 
           to-day&#8212;Sidney Morse<ptr target="n0862"/> the sculptor is here<ptr target="loc.01156_n2"/>
                &#8212;I hear from<ptr target="loc.01156_n3"/> Dr B<ptr target="n0119"/>and Kennedy<ptr target="n3039"/></p>
            <closer>
                <signed>W W</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.01156.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
